Time Complexity:

Let n = number of nodes in linked list

    Single traversal → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Using dummy nodes only (no extra data structure)

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Create two dummy nodes:
   - odd list (for positions 1,3,5…)
   - even list (for positions 2,4,6…)

2. Use two pointers:
   - t1 → builds odd list
   - t2 → builds even list

3. Traverse the list using pointer i:
   - Add current node to odd list
   - Move i forward
   - Add next node to even list (if exists)
   - Move i forward again

4. Continue until list ends

5. Connect end of odd list to start of even list:
   - t1.next = even.next

6. Return head of odd list:
   - odd.next






/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * public class ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode next;
 *     ListNode() {}
 *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    public ListNode oddEvenList(ListNode head) {
        ListNode odd = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode even = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode t1 = odd;
        ListNode t2 = even;
        ListNode i = head;
        while(i!=null){
            //odd list
            t1.next=i;
            t1=i;
            i=i.next;
            //even list
            t2.next=i;
            t2=i;
            if(i!=null) i=i.next;
        }
        t1.next=even.next;
        return odd.next;
    }
}
